{"id":"project-LICHEN-63wx","title":"announce.c: Potential mutex ordering issues between announce_mutex and ingest_mutex","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/announce.c
Lines: 283-336

In lichen_announce_ingest_authenticated(), mutexes are acquired in this order:
- Line 283: k_mutex_lock(&ingest_mutex, K_FOREVER);
- Line 284: k_mutex_lock(&announce_mutex, K_FOREVER);

This establishes the locking order as: ingest_mutex -> announce_mutex

However, looking at lichen_announce_reset() (lines 413-420):
- Line 415: k_mutex_lock(&announce_mutex, K_FOREVER);
- Line 418: k_mutex_lock(&observer_mutex, K_FOREVER);

And the observer_mutex is used separately in snapshot_observers (line 152).

The code alternates between holding ingest_mutex then announce_mutex, and holding just announce_mutex. If any future code path takes announce_mutex then ingest_mutex, this creates a deadlock risk.

Recommend documenting the required lock ordering and/or using a single mutex to simplify the locking strategy.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:50:03.977882Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:50:03.977914Z"}

